@node "Introduction" "Introduction to Window2Front"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Introduction"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Window2Front@{ub} is a tool that grabs a window and puts it in front of all the other ones.
So why another 'window to front' tool ? Well, sometimes I just wanna make something, no matter what.
---
This small util does it's job by selecting a hotkey.
Selecting the @{i}@{b}hotkey@{ub}@{ui} again automatically gets the next and the @{i}@{b}reverse hotkey@{ub}@{ui} the previous window.
And as this program is a commodity, you can change the hotkey by changing it in the icon and quit it when starting twice.
Default hotkey: @{b}CTRL, Y@{ub}.
Default reverse hotkey: @{b}CTRL, SHIFT, Y@{ub}.
---
This program handles a list up to 30 windows, which should be quite enough.
But if that's not enough for ya, let @{"me" link "Author" 0} know.

@endnode

